  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Safety Officer Cum ECO",
  "description": "<h4><strong>We are seeking a proactive and experienced Safety Officer cum Environmental Control Officer (ECO) to ensure a safe and environmentally compliant work environment. The ideal candidate will be responsible for overseeing safety protocols, monitoring environmental regulations, and ensuring compliance with both workplace safety standards and environmental practices.</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Educational Qualifications:</strong>A degree or diploma in Occupational Health and Safety, Environmental Science, or a related field.<br>\nAdditional certifications in safety or environmental management (e.g., NEBOSH, IOSH, ISO 14001, OSHA) are preferred.<br>\n</li>\n  <li><strong>Experience:</strong>Minimum of 2-3 years of experience in a safety officer or environmental control officer role, ideally within an industrial, manufacturing, or construction setting.<br>\nExperience in conducting safety audits, inspections, and environmental assessments.<br>\n</li>\n  <li><strong>Skills and Competencies:</strong>Strong knowledge of health, safety, and environmental regulations and best practices.<br>\nProficiency in risk assessment and the implementation of safety management systems.<br>\nStrong organizational and leadership skills with the ability to enforce safety protocols and maintain a culture of safety.<br>\nGood communication skills, both verbal and written, for training, reporting, and liaising with various stakeholders.<br>\nAbility to work under pressure and in potentially hazardous environments.<br>\nProficiency in Microsoft Office Suite (Excel, Word, PowerPoint).<br>\n</li>\n  <li><strong>Personal Attributes:</strong>Detail-oriented and capable of identifying safety and environmental hazards quickly.<br>\nStrong problem-solving skills, with the ability to suggest and implement corrective actions.<br>\nA team player with a proactive attitude and commitment to fostering a safe and sustainable workplace.<br>\nAbility to work independently and demonstrate initiative in handling safety and environmental challenges.<br>\n</li>\n  <li><strong>Additional Requirements:</strong>Certification in First Aid/CPR would be an advantage.<br>\nKnowledge of waste management systems, emergency response planning, and environmental impact assessments.<br>\n<strong>Educational Qualifications:A degree or diploma in Occupational Health and Safety, Environmental Science, or a related field.<br>\nAdditional certifications in safety or environmental management (e.g., NEBOSH, IOSH, ISO 14001, OSHA) are preferred.</strong><br>\n</li>\n</ul>",
